@node "features" "Features'n'Defects"

[ Features & Defects ]

Features:

 - GUI made with MUI, smart and highly configurable
 - ASL Popup File Requester
 - Fixed or Proportional fonts
 - Optional paragraph wordwrap
 - Configurable TAB length
 - 5 text buffers with smart gfx icons that allow a fast buffer switching.
 - Print functions
 - Search functions (forward, backward, from bottom, from top, highlighting...)
   with progress bar.
 - Numeric keypad support.
 - Able to run a configurable external editor
 - AppWindow
 - AppIcon
 - Unlimited parsing of Wb/Shell parameters.

Known Defects:

 - The buffers icons refresh is still too slow... Anyway, to improve it, I suggest
   to set simple refresh in  the MUI preferences and NOT to use Urouhack with file
   bitmap gadgets, because it makes run many programs up to 10 TIMES SLOWER.
 - The search routine is not too fast..
 - Apart from this, it's perfect! ;)

@endnode

@node "GUI" "Graphic User Interface"
@{b}The Main Window:@{ub}
The main window is divided in various areas that can be showed or hidden through
the  program  preferences.  All  the  functions  are available also in the popup
menus.

 @{u}-Buffers Bar@{uu}
   It shows graphically which buffers are free (the ones showing a disk), which are
   used  (the ones showing a text document) and which one is selected (the one with
   the magnify lens).
   If you click on the icon of a free buffer, a file requester will pop up allowing
   you to load a file in that buffer.
   If you click on the icon of a non-empty buffer, it will become the active buffer
   and its contents will be showed.
   If you click on the active buffer the search window will pop up, or if the search
   string is already set, the buffer will be searched for the next matching.
   If you drag a WB file icon on the image of a buffer, the file will be loaded.

 @{u}-Status Bar@{uu}
   It shows the name of the file in the active buffer or the program status (file
   loading, window refreshing..)

 @{u}-PopUp File Requester@{uu}
   It shows name and path of the active document.  You  can  load  a  new  file  by
   writing  its  name  in the string gadget or you can click on the requester popup
   gadget to open an ASL file requester.

 @{u}-Active buffer window@{uu}
   It shows the content of the file stored in the active buffer. You can use cursor
   keys,  numeric  pad  keys and MUI gadgets to scroll the text up and down. If you
   drag a file in this area, it will be loaded in the active buffer, while dragging
   various  files,  they  will  be  loaded  starting from the first buffer, as it's
   explained in the Running Program section.
   The same happens when files are dropped on the AppIcon of the iconified program.

@{b}The Preferences Window:@{ub}
It's divided in two parts: Main-Window preferences and Text preferences.

 @{u}-Main-Window Preferences:@{uu}
   4 checkmarks allow to select the areas of the main window that will be showed
   or hidden (ie: status bar, buffer bar, popup file requester).

 @{u}-Text Preferences@{uu}
  - Checkmark "Fixed Font": If selected, text will be  showed  using a  fixed
    width font (every character has the same width in pixel).
  - Checkmark "Justify Text": If selected, text will be justified.
  - "TAB length" slider     : sets the tab length (in number of spaces)
  - "Text Editor" string gadget: The command to  invoke  the  external  editor. You
    have to supply the file name as %f (Ex: c:ed %f).

  In the lower part of the window there are 3 buttons:

  - Save    -> Save all the changes to disk.
  - Use     -> Use the changes without saving them to disk.
  - Cancel  -> Discard all the changes made.

@{b}The Search Window:@{ub}
The Search Window is divided in three parts:

 @{u}-Status Bar@{uu}
    Shows the completion percentage of the search process.

 @{u}-Main Area@{uu}
   - "Look for" string gadget         : Write here the text you want to look for.
   - "Search" button                  : Search next occurence of the given string.
   - "Search Direction" cyclic gadget : Up stands for search backward, Down for
                                        search forward.
   - "From The Beginning" button      : Looks for the given string starting from the
                                        top of the document.
   - "From The End" button            : Looks for the given string starting from the
                                        bottom of the document.

  @{u}-Options Area@{uu}
    - "HighLighting mode" cyclic gadget

              o Don't Mark  ->  Searching stops at the first occurrence of the
                                search string.
              o Mark        ->  Searching stops on every occurrence of the search
                                string and the text found is highlighted.
              o Mark All    ->  All the occurrences of the search string are
               (no stop)        highlighted.


@{b}The Print Window:@{ub}
It only features a gadget showing the complection percentage of the print
process, and the abort button to stop printing.

@endnode

@node "History" "The Past, The Present.. dA Future.."
[ The Past of MUI More ]

   o @{b}0.1 - 0.7@{ub} (Internal releases)
   o @{b}0.8@{ub} (First public beta)

   o @{b}0.9@{ub} (Second public beta)
      o Case insensitive search
      o Many bug fixed
      o Boh

   o @{b}0.95@{ub} (3rd public beta)
      o Multibuffers added
      o TAB support added
      o Search routine improved
      o Justified text
      o The program detects an icon dropped in its window, but it reacts bad :)

   o @{b}0.97@{ub} (4th public beta - 27 august 1996) Major Update !
      o Preferences changed
      o You can launch an external editor from Mui More

      o Pg Up, Pg Dn, Home, End handled on the numeric keyboard (I cant handle
        return or spacebar :[ )
      o Improved the internal variables system.. Some variables were handled
        bad and could trash the memory!
      o File name with path of the active buffer is showed in the window title
      o AppWindow e Appicon:
         o Dragging a WB icon in the text window, the file will be loaded
           in the active buffer
         o Dragging more than 1 WB icon in the text window, the files will
           be loaded starting from the first buffer
         o Dragging an WB icon on one of the buffers icon, the file will be
           loaded in the respective buffer
         o Dragging an icon on the AppIcon while the program is iconified
           acts as the icon was dragged into the text window
      o The file path is no longer showed under the text window, only the file
        name is showed.
      o If the program is run without arguments, a file requester will popup
      o Bubble Help
      o AppIcon/AppWindow code rewritten from scratch.. 10k gained!
      o Icon images changed a bit
      o Icon images are hardcoded in the program, in this way we gain HD
        space, the program is loaded faster and images have no longer to
        be copied in a directory.
      o If env:mui/appmuimore.info is found, it will be used as appicon
      o Fixed free buffer function that sometimes worked bad
      o Muimore can be made resident with 'resident muimore PURE'

   o @{b}1.00@{ub} Amy Resource Special Edition (1st september 1996)
      o File requester remembers last dir and file opened
      o File requester opens on the same screen of the program
      o If a  drawer or device icon is dragged in the appwindow, a requester
        pointing to that drawer or device will be opened
      o The same happens if a device or drawer is given as WB argument
      o File requester hides #?.info files
      o Fixed a small bug in FreeBuffer function
      o Lightly changed menus, 'continue search' option added
      o Optimised the utilization of variables in the search routine

   o @{b}1.02@{ub} (6th september 1996)
      o Optimised the utilization of some variables
      o Totally changed the way in which the program detects the pression
        of a buffer button: now a hook it's used in spite of the old
        stupid handler
      o Search routine lightly changed
      o Small filerequester bug fixed
      o When you click on the active buffer icon and the search string is
        already set, the program will continue searching

   o @{b}1.05@{ub} (9th october 1996)
      o Finally I got the 040 back and I can use Enforcer again! :)
      o Highlights are made only at the end of the search process. In this
        way the entire search is much faster
      o Fixed some enforcer hits in the search routine.
      o Fixed a little refresh bug that occurred when the program was run
        with WB arguments
      o Print function added
      o Program checked for about 1 hour with Enforcer+GuardianAngel without
        any hit!!
      o Many ways of printing tried.. Choosen the synchronous one
      o Fixed enforcer hit that occurred on program starting if no arguments
        were passed
      o Localization added (english strings are hardcoded)
      o Made Italian catalog


   o @{b}1.10@{ub} (8th november 1996) Release version.

      o Fixed a small bug in the Italian catalog that didnt show hotkeys
        in menus (Thanks to Pierluigi Giuliana)
      o There were two equal hotkeys, fixed (Thanks to Pierluigi Giuliana)
      o Small changes in the GUI code

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Things to do:

(In order of implementation):

   o Change the Listview with MCC NewListView.. This would lead to a lot of
     improvementes (like clipboard support, horizontal scrollers..) but I
     should have to include that class in the archive, making it even bigger.
     I'm not sure if it's really worth, let me know..
   o Improve the refresh routine (I'll have to write from scratch a my own
     class)
   o Add multiselection to file requesters
   o Improve printing routines
   o Improve search routines
   o Add %s code to the external editor configuration to pass the public screen
     used by MuiMore
   o Drag & Drop of GUI elements (Ibrowse like)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Known bugs:

   o On certain Amigas, MuiMore gurus in search mode. I haven't still figured
     out why it  happens,  so  if you  encounter such problem, please let me
     know and try to describe in the most accurate way your hardware/software
     configuration and  the situation in which the guru occurred.
@endnode

@node "install" "MuiMore Installation"
[ MuiMore Installation ]

To install the program copy the catalog of your language (MUIMore_110/catalogs/
your_language/Muimore.catalog) to locale:catalogs/your_language/
Then copy MuiMore wherever you want and use it.. use it.. use it..

Anyway I think that next versions of MuiMore will feature an installation
script, even because the files to install will grow (buffers images).
@endnode

@node "intro" "Introduction"
[ What MuiMore is? ]

MuiMore is a text viewer with a lot of features that many advanced text  viewers
are  still  missing. We have given importance to the GUI in spite of the program
size, to make it userfriendly and at the same time pleasing to use.
There were already a lot of text viewers short in size, fast and functional, but
none  of them  pleased me because of their ugly graphic interfaces, so I decided
to code MY OWN text viewer..
I hope you like it as I do..

To know all the features of MuiMore have a look at @{"Features" link "features" 0}..

@endnode

