- The program cant be included in commercial packages without asking the author
  first.


@endnode

@node "start" "Running Program"
[ Running Program ]

MuiMore can be run from Shell or WorkBench.

You can pass as arguments all the files you want to open. Consider that
only the first 5 files that are accessible will be loaded.

Ex: Muimore s:foo.bar c:pippo.txt ram:kt.s

From Wb, arguments can be passed shift clicking the icons of the files
you want to open and then double clicking on MuiMore icon.

If no arguments are supplied, a file requester will pop up to select the
file you want to open.
@endnode

@node "traduttori" "Looking for Translator..."
[ MuiMore Transalations ]

Actually MuiMore has been translated only in English (Built In) and in Italian.
If you want to translate program and documentation in any other language, feel
free to @{"contact me" link "Autore" 0} and I will  send you the 'catalog descriptor' to  make the
translation.
I have decided not to include  the catalog descriptor in  the Mui More release,
to be able to coordinate the work of translators.
@endnode

